lead_paragraph: A picture caption in some copies on Nov. 14 with an article about Penn’s football program in the years after a popular player killed himself misidentified the team’s opponent. The photograph showed the player, Kyle Ambrogi, being congratulated after scoring in a game against Villanova, not against Bucknell. (Ambrogi killed himself on Oct. 10, 2005, two days after a game against Bucknell.).
